OL,6,F"I'm not saying that we should get rid
OL,7,Fof the Scouts or anything like that
OL,8,Fbecause they can do a lot of good."
OL,10,FScott was 11 when he went on a camping
OL,11,Ftrip at Ashworth Valley. He went for a
OL,12,Fmorning walk with a group and one
OL,13,Fleader and fell 60ft down a ravine.
OL,15,FSharon tells ITV News: "I said to one
OL,16,Fof the other adults that was there on
OL,17,Fthe day I said, 'I'm really quite
OL,18,Fworried about letting him go for the
OL,19,Fweekend'. And then he said, 'Sharon,
OL,20,Fnothing can go wrong'."
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G5/9
